      "type": "ApplicabilityConstraint",
      "name": "VAD hemolysis CFD applicability domain",
      "description": "The CFD hemolysis model is applicable to centrifugal blood pumps operating with human whole blood (hematocrit 35–45%) at physiological temperatures (36–38 °C). The model is restricted to operating points within the validated flow range (2–8 L/min) and rotational speed range (2000–3500 RPM). Predictions are not applicable to axial-flow pumps, non-Newtonian blood substitutes, or operating conditions outside the validated envelope. Absolute hemolysis index predictions are valid only when inlet turbulence intensity is below 5% and when shear stress exposure time is computed via Lagrangian particle tracking with a minimum of 5000 seeding particles per operating point."
    },
