    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Monte Carlo global sensitivity analysis — COU2 hemolysis index",
    "description": "A Sobol-index-based global sensitivity analysis was performed using N=10,000 Monte Carlo samples drawn from the joint distribution of six uncertain input parameters: blood viscosity (CV 8%), red blood cell fragility coefficient (CV 12%), turbulence model constant C_mu (±15% uniform), mesh resolution level (discrete: coarse/medium/fine/extra-fine), inlet velocity profile shape (Womersley order 1–4), and power-law hemolysis exponent alpha (0.62–0.78 uniform). The dominant first-order Sobol indices ranked as: hemolysis exponent alpha (S1=0.41), RBC fragility coefficient (S1=0.29), turbulence model constant (S1=0.18), blood viscosity (S1=0.07), inlet profile shape (S1=0.03), mesh level (S1=0.02). Total-order indices confirmed no significant higher-order interactions beyond alpha × fragility (ST interaction contribution 0.09). The 95th-percentile hemolysis index prediction interval is ±23% of the mean, driven primarily by uncertainty in the power-law damage exponent; this interval was propagated into the decision margin assessment.",
    "method": "Sobol variance-decomposition via quasi-random Saltelli sampling",
    "dominantFactors": [
      "hemolysis power-law exponent alpha",
      "RBC fragility coefficient",
      "turbulence model constant C_mu"
    ],
    "sampleSize": 10000
  },
